sickening. As far as players rights are concerned, we all pay every month to play, and that ten bucks buys each player his or her rights to do as he or she wishes in eq, now, i'm not saying that they can do *anything* they want, but, none of us has the right to say that anyone else can't go wherever they want. Now, if we were roleplaying, i think that there would be a more interesting edge to it, say, (for example), that Evoluxa and SR both wanted to kill trak, on the same day, there's nothing to stop either raiding party from going after him, the only thing they have to fear is they're reputations being hurt. Furthermore, I'd like to see somebody, in particular, a group of mostly indies say &quot;We beat (fill in guild name here) to trak for the kill&quot;. I don't like the fact that guilds are the ruling class in eq. How many guild members here even remember the purpose for their guild, (or mission statement if you want to call it that), and those of you that do remember it, how many of you actually stick to that code, I know that i couldn't tell you my guilds purpose anymore, and i doubt that we even follow traditions anymore. I'm not trying to offend anyone, (mostly because i do recognize that guilds are the ruling class, and i don't want to be excluded from anything in the future for stating my opinion), but, brell is starting to feel like it's being carved up into bits of timeshare condos, &quot;you can have trak on the evenings of the the 2nd and 4th spawns of the month, and we'll take him on the first and third, and if there is a 5th spawn, it's FFA, sound good??&quot;, and frankly, i don't want to see a very fun game turned into something that feels like a corporation. Some of the guilds are beginning to remind me of verant, and we all know how evil verant can be, (j/k).<br>
OK, I'm done with my tangent now, goodnight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usstiyrr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sstiyrr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/28/01 1:16:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Indies on Dragon Rotations</span><hr size=1> Ok, guys, lets take it straight.<br>
<br>
Baldaaf, thanks for your arguments, you said anyone should have the same rights.<br>
So, why do guilds get the shaft? I have the same right toi sign up as any Indy, according to your argument. So has every other member of any other guild. this would give like 60 signups for ET alone, just to get same rights as indy's.<br>
<br>
Indy's on lists is plain unfair to guildmembers, unless every single guildmember can sign up on his own !<br>
<br>
Thats my personal opinion ! <p><BR>
