<br>
Its also been brought up on MANY other threads about Indies.  The logic is flawed.  If non-guilded players have rights just because they pay $10 a month then EVERYONE has those rights, guilded or non-guilded.  Obviously we dont want a guild of 40 having 40 slots so they are restricted in order to have a system that attempts to be as fair as possible to everyone.  Why should guildmembers be restricted and not non-guildmembers in order to have a system that attempts to be as fair as possible to everyone?  Why should a guild of 40 be given one spot yet 40 indies can have 40 spots? Why should 3 guilds of 10 get 3 slots while 1 guild of 30 gets 1 slot?<br>
<br>
Most of the guilds on the Vox/Naggy lists are on their 2nd or 3rd or more shot at Vox/Naggy.  I say remove the dragons from the rotations.  They would die alot faster and those that want to put the effort in would get the reward.<br>
